<subSubSection id="C368652E93558E08F2AAFF4DFB00FED6" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2AAFF4DFB00FED6" blockId="12.[151,1437,223,502]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893558E08F2AAFF4DFB1CFED6" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147308" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
The specimen here recognized as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F026FF4DFDACFF32" box="[539,637,223,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">holotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing the labels “ex-Museo Chaudoir”, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693558E08F6E2FF4DFA89FF32" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[1247,1368,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lusitanicus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793558E08F6E2FF4DFA89FF32" box="[1247,1368,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">lusitanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Lusitania”, “Schüppel” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F3E6FE91FD97FED6" box="[475,582,259,285]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693558E08F056FE91FBD0FED6" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[619,1025,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lusitanicus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793558E08F056FE91FCB0FED6" box="[619,865,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Acupalpus lusitanicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F154FE91FBD0FED6" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[873,1025,259,285]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<collectorName id="2687537393558E08F631FE96FBADFED6" box="[1036,1148,259,286]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">J. Serrano</collectorName>
vidit.”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93558E08F2FAFEB5FADFFE3E" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2FAFEB5FA51FEAD" blockId="12.[151,1437,223,502]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893558E08F2FAFEB5FAA8FEAE" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147338" collectorName="M. Schuppel" country="Portugal" location="Portugal" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
The recognition of this specimen as the 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F0B4FEB5FD3AFE8A" box="[649,747,295,321]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">holotype</typeStatus>
of the species is based on the statement of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F6EEFEB5FAA8FE8A" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[1235,1401,295,321]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean (1829)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<emphasis id="B906EAB793558E08F7BEFEBAFAA8FEAE" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
Je ne possède qu’un individu mâle de cet insecte, qui m’a été envoyé pai’ 
<collectorName id="2687537393558E08F18DFEDEFBEEFEAE" box="[944,1087,331,357]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">M. Schuppel</collectorName>
, comme venant du 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593558E08F728FED9FAA8FEAE" box="[1301,1401,331,357]" name="Portugal" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Portugal</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2FAFEFDFC96FE1A" blockId="12.[151,1437,223,502]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
The characteristics of the 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F3D0FEFDFD9EFE42" box="[493,591,367,393]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">holotype</typeStatus>
slightly differ from those described in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F633FEFDFAFEFE42" author="Serrano, J. &amp; Ortuno, V. M." box="[1038,1327,367,393]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" pagination="337 - 348" refId="ref12386" refString="Serrano, J. &amp; Ortuno, V. M. (2001) Revision de las especies ibericas de Bradycellus Erichson (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Harpalini). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 106, 337 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 2001.16775" type="journal article" year="2001">Serrano &amp; Ortuño (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, in that it has a pronotum side less rounded and the posterior angle is more marked, not so rounded. Keys to the species see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F2AAFE2AFEE6FE1A" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[151,311,439,466]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F37CFE25FE3CFE19" author="Antoine, M." box="[321,493,439,466]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine (1959)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F019FE25FC92FE1A" author="Serrano, J. &amp; Ortuno, V. M." box="[548,835,439,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" pagination="337 - 348" refId="ref12386" refString="Serrano, J. &amp; Ortuno, V. M. (2001) Revision de las especies ibericas de Bradycellus Erichson (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Harpalini). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 106, 337 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 2001.16775" type="journal article" year="2001">Serrano &amp; Ortuño (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2FAFE4EFADFFE3E" blockId="12.[151,1437,223,502]" box="[199,1294,475,502]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
It is distributed in the Iberian Peninsula, the Maghreb and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593558E08F186FE49FC3FFE3E" box="[955,1006,475,501]" name="Italy" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F1C0FE49FAD3FE3E" author="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M." box="[1021,1282,475,502]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" pagination="1837" refId="ref10991" refString="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M. (2017) Subtribe Stenolophina Kirby, 1837. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 562 - 577." type="book chapter" year="2017">Jaeger &amp; Kataev, 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
